OL,3,CHundreds take part in Selkirk run for
OL,4,CBorders charity worker
OL,6,FHer husband Roy Ledsham said: "Her
OL,7,Fwhole life really was working towards
OL,8,Fhelping people with learning
OL,9,Fdisabilities and making sure they
OL,10,Ffulfilled themselves as much as they
OL,11,Fcould.
OL,13,F"Last year it was such a warm lovely
OL,14,Fevent and people seemed really keen to
OL,15,Fcome again this year to remember
OL,16,FCharmian and all that she did."
OL,18,FThere were more than 200 participants,
OL,19,Fmuch more than the number anticipated
OL,20,Fby organisers.
